paragraph.text:
The temporary increase in the membership of the House of Representatives provided under paragraph (1) shall not operate to either increase or decrease the permanent membership of the House of Representatives as prescribed in the 
              Act of August 8, 1911 (37 Stat. 13; 
                2 U.S.C. 2
              ), nor shall such temporary increase affect the basis of reapportionment established by the 
              Act of November 15, 1941 (55 Stat. 761; 
                2 U.S.C. 2a
              ), for the 82nd Congress and each Congress thereafter.
